  "prompt": "Internet data stream?",
  "response": "An internet data stream refers to a continuous flow of data transmitted over the internet from a source to a destination. This can include various types of data such as video, audio, text, or other forms of digital content. Data streams are used for applications like live video streaming, online gaming, real-time communication, and more. They enable real-time or near-real-time delivery of data, allowing users to access and interact with content as it is being transmitted. Protocols such as HTTP Live Streaming (HLS), Real-Time Messaging Protocol (RTMP), and WebRTC are commonly used to facilitate internet data streaming.",
